(484, 12, 'tnc_desc_2', '<p>At Knowtical, we are committed to ensuring transparency and clarity regarding the use of cookies on our website. This Cookie Policy outlines the types of cookies we use, why we use them, and how you can control or delete cookies.</p>\n<h4><strong>What Are Cookies?</strong></h4>\n<p>Cookies are small text files that are placed on your device (computer, smartphone, tablet) when you visit a website. These files contain information about your browsing activity on that site. Cookies serve various purposes, including improving website functionality, analyzing website usage, and personalizing your experience.</p>\n<h4><strong>Why Do We Use Cookies?</strong></h4>\n<p>We use cookies for several reasons:</p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Essential Cookies:</strong> These cookies are necessary for the basic functionality of our website. They enable core features such as page navigation, security, and accessibility.</li>\n<li><strong>Performance Cookies:</strong> These cookies help us understand how visitors interact with our website by collecting anonymous data. We use this information to improve our website\'s performance and user experience.</li>\n<li><strong>Functionality Cookies:</strong> These cookies allow our website to remember choices you make (such as language preferences) and provide enhanced, personalized features.</li>\n<li><strong>Targeting/Advertising Cookies:</strong> We may use these cookies to deliver advertisements relevant to your interests. They may also be used to track the effectiveness of our advertising campaigns.</li>\n</ol>\n<h4><strong>What Types of Cookies Do We Use?</strong></h4>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Session Cookies:</strong> These cookies are temporary and are deleted when you close your browser.</li>\n<li><strong>Persistent Cookies:</strong> These cookies remain on your device for a specified period or until you delete them.</li>\n<li><strong>First-party Cookies:</strong> These cookies are set by the website you are visiting.</li>\n<li><strong>Third-party Cookies:</strong> These cookies are set by domains other than the one you are visiting, such as advertisers or social media platforms.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4><strong>How to Control Or Delete Cookies</strong></h4>\n<p>You have the ability to control or delete cookies through your browser settings. However, please note that disabling cookies may affect the functionality and performance of our website. You can typically manage cookie settings in your browser preferences. Each browser is different, so please refer to your browser\'s help menu for instructions on how to modify your cookie settings.</p>\n<h4><strong>Changes to This Cookie Policy</strong></h4>\n<p>We may update this Cookie Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or for legal reasons. Any updates will be posted on this page, and the \"Last Updated\" date will be revised accordingly. We encourage you to review this policy periodically to stay informed about how we use cookies.</p>\n<h4><strong>Cookies That Have Been Set In the Past</strong></h4>\n<p>If you have disabled one or more Cookies, we may still use information collected from cookies prior to your disabled preference being set, however, we will stop using the disabled cookie to collect any further information.</p>'),
