(492, 12, 'tnc_desc_6', 'Please review these Terms carefully as they serve as an enforceable contract between us and contain important information about your legal rights, remedies, and obligations.\n\nKnowticals mission is to improve lives through learning. We enable anyone anywhere to create and share educational content (instructors) and to access that educational content to learn (students). We consider our model the best way to offer valuable educational content to our users. We need rules to keep our platform and services safe for you, us, and our student and instructor community. These Terms apply to all your activities on the Knowtical website, the Knowtical mobile applications, our TV applications, our APIs, and other related services (Services).\n\nIf you publish a course on the Knowtical platform, you must also agree to the Instructor Terms. We also provide details regarding our processing of personal data of our students and instructors in our Privacy Policy. If you are using Knowtical as part of your employers Knowtical Business learning and development program, you can consult our Knowtical Business Privacy Statement. Our Instructor Terms, Privacy Policy, and other Knowtical policies applicable to your use of our Services are incorporated by reference into these Terms.\n\nOur website and apps cause communications about your browsing and app activities and app usage to be sent from you to third parties who provide services to Knowtical. By using our Services, you consent to these communications.\n\n1. Accounts\nYou need an account for most activities on our platform. Keep your password secure, as youre responsible for all activity associated with your account. If you suspect someone else is using your account, notify our Support Team immediately. You must have reached the age of consent for online services in your country to use Knowtical Learning.\nTo participate in most activities on our platform, including purchasing and accessing content or submitting content for publication, you need an account. When creating and maintaining your account, you must provide accurate and complete information, including a valid email address. You are fully responsible for your account and everything that occurs on it, including any harm or damage caused by someone using your account without your permission. This means keeping your password secure. You may not transfer your account to someone else or use someone elses account. If you request access to an account, we will only grant it if you can provide sufficient information to prove you are the owner. In the event of a user\'s death, their account will be closed.\nYou may not share your account login credentials with anyone else. You are responsible for what happens with your account, and Knowtical Learning will not intervene in disputes between students or instructors who have shared account login credentials. Notify us immediately if you learn someone else may be using your account without your permission or if you suspect any other breach of security by contacting our Support Team. We may request information to confirm you are the account owner.\nStudents and instructors must be at least 18 years old to create an account on Knowtical Learning and use our services. If you are younger than 18 but above the age of consent for online services in your country, you may not set up an account but can invite a parent or guardian to open an account to help you access appropriate content. If you are below this age of consent, you may not create a Knowtical Learning account. If we discover you have created an account in violation of these rules, we will terminate it. Under our Instructor Terms, you may be requested to verify your identity before submitting content for publication on Knowtical Learning.\nYou can terminate your account at any time by following the steps outlined in our Privacy Policy to understand what happens when you terminate your account.\n2. Content Enrollment and Lifetime Access\nWhen you enroll in a course or other content, you receive a license from us to view it via the Knowtical Learning platform and services. This license is for personal use only and cannot be transferred or resold in any way. We generally grant you lifetime access, except when content must be disabled due to legal or policy reasons or for enrollments via Subscription Plans.\nUnder our Instructor Terms, when instructors publish content on Knowtical Learning, they grant Knowtical Learning a license to offer that content to students. This means we have the right to sublicense the content to enrolled students. As a student, when you enroll in a course or other content, whether free or paid, you are getting a license from Knowtical Learning to view the content via our platform and services. Content is licensed, not sold, to you. This license does not give you any right to resell the content in any manner, including by sharing account information or illegally downloading and sharing it.\nIn legal terms, Knowtical Learning grants you (as a student) a limited, non-exclusive, non-transferable license to access and view the content for which you have paid all required fees, solely for your personal, non-commercial, educational purposes through our services, in accordance with these Terms and any conditions or restrictions associated with the content. All other uses are expressly prohibited. You may not reproduce, redistribute, transmit, assign, sell, broadcast, rent, share, lend, modify, adapt, edit, create derivative works of, sublicense, or otherwise transfer or use any content unless we give you explicit permission in a written agreement signed by an authorized Knowtical Learning representative. This also applies to content you can access via any of our APIs.\nWe generally provide a lifetime access license to our students when they enroll in a course or other content. However, we reserve the right to revoke any license to access and use content at any time if we