(1025, 12, 'tnc_desc_3', '<p>The following terms apply to all Knowtical and Knowtical-affiliated scholarship programs. Please see the individual scholarship rules for additional eligibility criteria. Application to a Knowtical scholarship program constitutes an agreement to all of the following terms and conditions:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Knowtical, Inc. and/or scholarship sponsors (&ldquo;Sponsors&rdquo;) may offer scholarships from time-to-time to the public or a portion thereof to be used toward Knowtical programs and courses.</li>\n<li>Eligibility criteria may vary per program and will be available on the individual scholarship web page. All eligibility criteria must be met by the application deadline.</li>\n<li>Scholarship awards are not redeemable or refundable for cash and may not be applied to any program other than the program for which the scholarship was awarded. Knowtical will not be responsible for any taxes levied against the recipient by the recipient\'s government or taxing authority. Scholarship winners will be responsible for any additional educational expenses.</li>\n<li>Scholarship winners can only win one scholarship per scholarship contest or offering but may apply for multiple scholarships at the same time or at different times.</li>\n<li>Scholarship awards are final and non-transferable.</li>\n<li>Applicant agrees that all information contained in the application is true to the best of the applicant&rsquo;s knowledge, and that application materials that require demonstration of proficiency will be the original work of the applicant.</li>\n<li>Applicant acknowledges that names of scholarship winners may be listed on Knowtical&rsquo;s websites.</li>\n<li>If Knowtical is partnering with a Sponsor, submitted applications and program performance data, including applicant information, may be shared with that Sponsor. Applicants consent to the sharing of this data.</li>\n<li>Applicants acknowledge that access to the Knowtical platform is governed by the Knowtical <a href=\"https://www.knowtical.com/legal/terms-of-use\">Terms of Use</a> and <a href=\"https://www.knowtical.com/legal/privacy\">Privacy Policy</a>.</li>\n<li>Knowtical reserves the right to revoke awards if a winner no longer meets the eligibility criteria or if there is a breach of these or other Knowtical terms.</li>\n<li>Knowtical employees are ineligible to apply for any Knowtical scholarship programs.</li>\n<li>Applicants who are subject to or reside in countries subject to U.S. trade restrictions are ineligible to apply for any Knowtical scholarships.</li>\n<li>Applicant acknowledges and agrees that participation in a sponsored scholarship does not create any relationship, partnership, or privity with the Sponsor and applicant will hold Sponsor harmless in any dispute arising from the scholarship contest or offering.</li>\n<li>Applicant agrees that any dispute with Knowtical regarding any scholarship contest or offering will be first addressed through negotiation in good faith, and, if no resolution results from that negotiation within thirty (30) days, then by arbitration administered by JAMS, in accordance with JAMS Streamlined Arbitration Rules and Procedures, excluding any rules or procedures governing or permitting class actions.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If there are any questions about these terms or any individual scholarship requirements, please reach out to the Scholarships team by <strong>submitting a ticket.</strong></p>'),
(1026, 12, '_tnc_desc_3', 'field_66830992bf2c2'),
(1027, 12, 'tnc_desc_4', '<p>By enrolling in a Knowtical program or Online Course, or otherwise accessing the Knowtical platform or interacting with any of the Knowtical Services, you agree to abide by the following Knowtical Honor Code, which we created to ensure the best learning experience for you and for all other Knowtical Students (as defined in our Terms of Use). Students found to be acting in violation of the terms set forth may be asked to leave their program without a refund. By using Knowtical, you also agree to our Terms of Use, including the User Conduct Policy, and, if you participate in any of our communities, the Community Code of Conduct. Please conduct yourself responsibly and employ common-sense when participating in any Knowtical community or program. You further understand and agree that all decisions regarding participation, graduation, and awarding of verified certificates will be made by Knowtical in its sole discretion.</p>\n<p>You agree that you:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>will not harass other Students, Attendees, Visitors, or Knowtical Employees;</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>will not cheat on any assignment, projects, or assessments, as applicable, for the Online Courses. For example, giving or receiving unpermitted aid on, or copying or sharing of, another User&rsquo;s (as defined in the Terms of Use) projects or other class work (or any portion thereof);</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>will not plagiarize (a form of cheating) the work of others. For example, using another person&rsquo;s original work (e.g., code, language, formulas, etc.) in your assignments, projects, or assessments. For more information on plagiarism, see our full definition and examples here.</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>will not post online any secured testing materials, as applicable;</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>will comply with the requirements of the specific applicable code of conduct, if any, relating directly to a Nanodegree program in which such you are enrolled; and</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>will notify the instructors immediately if you become aware of any other User cheating or breaching this Honor Code or the Terms of Use.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you are registered or enrolled as a Student in, or are otherwise attending, an Online Course through an Educational Partner or other institution with its own policy regarding student and/or employee conduct or an \"honor code,\" those terms may also apply to you.</p>\n<p>Failure to adhere to this Honor Code impairs the integrity of our learning environment and harms the value of our Nanodegree programs for our Students. If we determine that you have violated this Honor Code, we reserve the right to take any action we deem appropriate, including, but not limited to, rejecting your submissions or removing you from our programs with no refund.</p>'),
(1028, 12, '_tnc_desc_4', 'field_6683099abf2c3'),
(1029, 12, 'tnc_desc_5', '<p>At Knowtical Learning (\"Knowtical Learning,\" \"we,\" \"us,\" \"our\"), we value your privacy rights. This privacy policy (\"Privacy Policy\") is designed to outline how we handle the information collected and received from your use of our Services (as defined in our Terms of Use or \"TOU\") provided through our website,<a href=\"http://www.knowtical.com\"> http://www.knowtical.com</a>, and any other websites or applications we own, operate, or control (the \"Website(s)\"). Please note that this Privacy Policy applies solely to the Services, and we are not accountable for the practices of individuals, companies, institutions, or websites not under our control, management, or employment. Capitalized terms not defined herein have the meanings ascribed to them in the TOU.</p>\n<p>Kindly read this Privacy Policy and our TOU thoroughly, as they govern your use of Knowtical Learning. If you do not agree to this Privacy Policy, we kindly ask you not to use our Services.</p>\n<p>Knowtical Learning, Inc. acts as the data controller of your information. Additional details can be found in the \"Contact Information\" section below. Please be aware that if you access our Services through Sponsored Services or our Employee and Enterprise Sponsored Access Services, the third party sponsoring your participation in the Online Courses may furnish us with information subject to our agreement with them, thereby making the third-party sponsor the controller regarding such data.</p>\n<h3><strong>Important Information About Using Our Services</strong></h3>\n<p>By submitting any information to us, you acknowledge that we may collect, use, disclose, and retain such information in accordance with this Privacy Policy and our TOU, as well as permitted or required by law. If you do not agree with these terms, please refrain from providing any information to us. We may offer social sharing features as part of our Services, allowing you to make your career Profile (as described below in the Profiles and Career Services Section) public and share your details and information, including your Online Course progress, with others outside of the Knowtical Learning Website(s) (\"Social Sharing\"). By choosing to participate in any of our Social Sharing Services, you acknowledge that any information or materials you include in your Profile can be viewed by other individuals accessing the Website(s), including potential or current employers, as well as others on relevant third-party websites. You also recognize that information shared through Social Services may remain accessible on third-party websites and/or to those with whom you\'ve shared the information, even if you make your Profile private after previously making it public and/or cease sharing your information, and that Knowtical Learning has no control over the access or use of information provided to third parties via Social Sharing outside its Website(s).</p>\n<h3><strong>What Information We Collect</strong></h3>\n<h4><strong>Information You Provide Us</strong></h4>\n<p>We collect various information directly from you, including:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Name, address, telephone number, and email address</li>\n<li>Log-in credentials, if you register a User Account with us</li>\n<li>Details of purchases or other transactions, such as your shipping address (please note, we do not collect, store, or transmit financial account information)</li>\n<li>Information related to customer service and maintenance interactions</li>\n<li>Demographic information, such as gender, socio-economic status, and other personal details</li>\n<li>Information provided in connection with any application or admissions process, including educational and work experience, prerequisite knowledge, pre-assessments, goals, and other relevant data</li>\n<li>Information submitted for career services, such as salary details, job placement information, career goals, work experience, and other pertinent information</li>\n<li>User-generated content uploaded or posted to public forums</li>\n<li>Any other information you choose to provide directly in connection with your use of the Services</li>\n</ul>\n<h4><strong>Participation in Online Courses</strong></h4>\n<p>If you wish to participate in an Online Course, you will be required to provide certain information necessary for conducting such a course, including your name and email address. Additionally, Knowtical or its third-party service providers may collect information from you related to assignments, exams, and other assessments associated with the Online Course. This may include verifying or authenticating your identity or submissions, monitoring your performance during exams, and collecting information about your performance or accomplishments related to the course.</p>\n<h4><strong>Profiles and Career Services</strong></h4>\n<p>You have the option to share additional information, such as work experience, resumes, transcripts, pictures, and answers to questions about your experience, studies, and work preferences, when creating a professional profile through our career services. This information can be shared by updating your Profile, uploading documents, or responding to questions or surveys presented through our Services. All information provided through career services is collectively referred to as your \"Profile.\" By choosing to make your Profile public, you acknowledge that it will be shared with and publicly viewed by third parties accessing the career services portal and the Services, including potential employers, recruiters, other students or individuals, and us. Employers and other third parties accessing the career services portal may contact you via the contact information provided in your Profile, and your Profile and associated information may be shared with employers, recruiters, or other career-related third parties.</p>\n<h4><strong>Information We Collect Through Automated Means</strong></h4>\n<h5><strong>Analytics Information</strong></h5>\n<p>When using our Services, we and our service providers may use cookies and similar technologies to track, collect, and aggregate certain information, including pages visited on our Website(s), the order in which they were visited, URLs linking to our Website(s), and hyperlinks clicked. This information may involve logging the IP address, operating system, and browser software used by each user of the Website. Through such information, we may determine a user\'s Internet Service Provider and general geographic location (city/state) of connectivity. These technologies help identify repeat visitors, the type of content and sites linked to, the duration of time spent on particular areas of our Website(s), and specific functionalities utilized by users.</p>\n<p>We utilize third-party web analytics services (e.g., Google Analytics) to collect and analyze usage information through cookies and similar tools, engage in auditing, research, or reporting, assist with fraud prevention, and provide certain features to you. Additionally, a limited amount of your information (such as email address and sign-up date) may be provided to Intercom, Inc. (\"Intercom\") for analysis of Website usage on our behalf, enabling us to enhance our Services. We may also use third-party services (including Intercom) for communication purposes, either via email or messages within our Service(s). The terms and conditions and privacy policy for such service providers should be reviewed carefully. If you wish to opt out of having information collected by or submitted to Intercom or have inquiries regarding other third-party service providers\' collection of your information for this purpose, please contact us. For more details about our use of cookies and similar technologies, including instructions on how to install the Google Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on to prevent Google from utilizing your information for analytics, or to control or disable cookies, please refer to our Cookies Policy.</p>\n<h5><strong>Online Advertising</strong></h5>\n<p>We may permit third-party companies, including advertising companies (e.g., Facebook, Google, Twitter, Quora, and Bing), to place cookies on our website. These cookies enable such companies to track your activity across various sites where they display ads and record your activities to show ads considered relevant to you as you browse the Internet. They store information about the content you browse together with an identifier linked to your device or IP address. Additionally, these cookies inform us and third parties whether you\'ve seen an ad or type of ad, and for how long it has been since you last saw an ad. This information aids in frequency capping, ad customization, and measuring ad effectiveness. For more information on online advertising and how you can manage or disable these cookies, please refer to our Cookies Policy.</p>\n<h5><strong>Do Not Track Signals</strong></h5>\n<p>At present, we do not monitor or take any action regarding Web browser signals or other mechanisms for expressing choice concerning the collection of information about an individual over time and across third-party websites or online services (e.g., Web browser \"do not track\" signals).</p>\n<h4><strong>Information We Collect from Social Media and Other Content Platforms</strong></h4>\n<p>If you log in to or connect to a third-party network (e.g., through a social network), or log in to our Services through a social network site (e.g., Facebook), you may allow us to access and store certain information from your social network profile. This may include your name, gender, profile picture, depending on your settings on such services. If you do not wish to share this information, please refrain from using a social networking connection to access the Services. Please refer to the privacy policies and terms of use of social networking sites for details on how they handle your information, as they may allow you to adjust your privacy settings.</p>\n<h4><strong>Referral Programs</strong></h4>\n<p>We may offer certain Users the opportunity to refer their friends (\"Referees\") to the Site through a third-party referral program, where both Referrers and Referees may obtain credits or other rewards through such referrals. To the extent we offer such programs, Referrers may share information about Referees, including email addresses, for the purpose of sharing the referral offer. We may also share the Referrer&rsquo;s email and name with the Referee and provide the Referrer confirmation of the Referee&rsquo;s acceptance of the referral, which may include the Referee&rsquo;s email, in connection with providing any such referral program.</p>\n<h3><strong>How We Utilize Collected Information</strong></h3>\n<p>We employ the information collected from and about you for various purposes, depending on the types of information gathered and the specific services you use. These purposes include:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Sending Information</strong>: Providing pertinent information regarding our services.</li>\n<li><strong>Responding to Communications</strong>: Promptly addressing inquiries and requests.</li>\n<li><strong>Managing Online Courses</strong>: Tracking attendance, progress, and completion, administering exams and assessments, and ensuring adherence to testing rules.</li>\n<li><strong>Providing Services</strong>: Delivering services requested in conjunction with Online Courses.</li>\n<li><strong>Contacting You</strong>: Reaching out via email, postal mail, or phone regarding products, services, surveys, promotions, and events.</li>\n<li><strong>Content Customization</strong>: Tailoring provided content.</li>\n<li><strong>Understanding Interests</strong>: Enhancing our understanding of user interests and needs to improve services.</li>\n<li><strong>Analysis and Research</strong>: Engaging in analysis, research, and reports regarding service usage.</li>\n<li><strong>Securing Services</strong>: Implementing measures to ensure service security.</li>\n<li><strong>Compliance</strong>: Abiding by applicable procedures, laws, and regulations.</li>\n<li><strong>Legal Rights</strong>: Establishing, exercising, or defending our legal rights.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4><strong>Combined Information</strong></h4>\n<p>For the purposes outlined, we may combine information collected through our services with data obtained from other sources, both online and offline, and utilize such combined information accordingly.</p>\n<h3><strong>How We Share and Disclose Your Information</strong></h3>\n<p>Your information is shared and disclosed in various ways, including:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Service Providers</strong>: Access granted to operations and maintenance contractors and other third parties performing services on our behalf.</li>\n<li><strong>Employers</strong>: Information may be shared during Online Courses if sponsored or paid for by employers.</li>\n<li><strong>Educational Institutions and Scholarship Partners</strong>: Sharing information with educational partners associated with specific courses.</li>\n<li><strong>Business Partners</strong>: With consent, sharing information to directly connect users with relevant third-party business partners.</li>\n<li><strong>Protection of Knowtical and Others</strong>: Accessing, retaining, and disclosing information as required by law or to protect rights, property, or safety.</li>\n<li><strong>Profiles and Career Services</strong>: Public profiles accessible to our network of hiring partners, including course performance and demographic details.</li>\n<li><strong>Related Entities and Affiliates</strong>: Information may be shared with affiliated companies under our common ownership or control.</li>\n<li><strong>Business Transfers</strong>: User information may be transferred in business development scenarios.</li>\n<li><strong>Aggregate/Anonymous Information</strong>: Sharing aggregate or anonymous information without restrictions for research, marketing purposes, or statistical analyses.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Data Subject Rights and Your Choices</strong></h3>\n<p>You may have certain rights concerning your information:</p>\n<h4><strong>Your Legal Rights</strong></h4>\n<p>If you would like further information regarding your legal rights under applicable law or wish to exercise them, please contact us. Your local laws may permit you to request access to certain information, prevent processing for direct-marketing purposes, update or delete information, restrict processing and disclosure, transfer information, or revoke consent.</p>\n<h4><strong>Communications &amp; Notification Preferences and Opting Out</strong></h4>\n<p>You have the opportunity to update information or opt out of having your contact information used for non-essential purposes. You can manage communication subscriptions through your account settings or by contacting us.</p>\n<h4><strong>Retention of Your Information</strong></h4>\n<p>We retain your information for the necessary processing purposes and as required by applicable laws.</p>\n<h3><strong>Third Party Links and Features</strong></h3>\n<p>Our services may contain links to third-party websites and integrations. We encourage reviewing the privacy policies and security practices of these third parties, as their collection, use, and disclosure of your information will be subject to their policies.</p>\n<h3><strong>Children\'s Privacy</strong></h3>\n<p>Our services are intended for general audiences and not for children under the age of 13. We comply with applicable age restrictions and requirements according to local laws.</p>\n<p>I appreciate your patience, and I apologize for any inconvenience caused by the incomplete response. Let me know if there\'s anything else you need assistance with!</p>\n<h3><strong>International User Data Handling</strong></h3>\n<p>Knowtical values the privacy of all users, including our international audience. When you use our services, please be aware that we store information on servers located in the United States. By utilizing our services, you consent to the storage of your data within the United States. If you access our services from outside the United States and the European Union, please note that your information will be transferred to and stored on servers in the United States or other countries. It\'s essential to recognize that data protection laws in these jurisdictions may differ from those in your own country. By submitting your data and using our services, you acknowledge and consent to the transfer, storage, and processing of your information in and to the United States.</p>\n<p>Knowtical may also engage service providers and others in countries outside your country of residence, including the United States, for data processing purposes. We ensure that such third parties adhere to appropriate data protection measures in line with this Privacy Policy. These measures may include implementing Standard Contractual Clauses in accordance with relevant data protection laws. For further information on these mechanisms, please contact us using the details provided in the \"Knowtical Contact Information\" section below. If applicable, you have the right to lodge a complaint with the data protection supervisory authority in your country or seek legal remedies if you believe your rights have been violated.</p>\n<h3><strong>Information Security Measures</strong></h3>\n<p>At Knowtical, safeguarding the confidentiality and security of your information is paramount. We implement a range of technical, administrative, and physical measures to protect your data from unauthorized access or disclosure. While we strive to ensure the security of your information, please be aware that no method of internet transmission or storage is entirely foolproof. Additionally, we may retain your information in our databases and systems even after deactivating your Knowtical account, as long as we have a legitimate purpose and in accordance with applicable law.</p>\n<h3><strong>Changes to Our Privacy Policy</strong></h3>\n<p>Please note that our privacy practices are subject to periodic review and may change over time. Any updates or modifications to our Privacy Policy will be effective immediately upon posting on our Website(s). You can check the \"Effective Date\" at the beginning of the document to see if any changes have been made since your last review. In the event of a material change, you will be provided with appropriate notice as required by law. By continuing to use our Services, you indicate that you have read and understood the latest version of this Privacy Policy. We encourage you to revisit this page periodically to stay informed about any updates.</p>\n<h3><strong>Knowtical Contact Information</strong></h3>\n<p>If you have any questions, comments, or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please don\'t hesitate to contact us:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Email: privacy@knowtical.com</li>\n<li>Knowtical Learning&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Attn: Privacy</p>\n<p>Rz-D 30B D-Block Dabri Extn East,&nbsp;</p>\n<p>New Delhi, Delhi - 110045, India</p>'),
