(1031, 12, 'tnc_desc_6', 'Please review these Terms carefully as they serve as an enforceable contract between us and contain important information about your legal rights, remedies, and obligations.\n\nKnowticals mission is to improve lives through learning. We enable anyone anywhere to create and share educational content (instructors) and to access that educational content to learn (students). We consider our model the best way to offer valuable educational content to our users. We need rules to keep our platform and services safe for you, us, and our student and instructor community. These Terms apply to all your activities on the Knowtical website, the Knowtical mobile applications, our TV applications, our APIs, and other related services (Services).\n\nIf you publish a course on the Knowtical platform, you must also agree to the Instructor Terms. We also provide details regarding our processing of personal data of our students and instructors in our Privacy Policy. If you are using Knowtical as part of your employers Knowtical Business learning and development program, you can consult our Knowtical Business Privacy Statement. Our Instructor Terms, Privacy Policy, and other Knowtical policies applicable to your use of our Services are incorporated by reference into these Terms.\n\nOur website and apps cause communications about your browsing and app activities and app usage to be sent from you to third parties who provide services to Knowtical. By using our Services, you consent to these communications.\n\n1. Accounts\nYou need an account for most activities on our platform. Keep your password secure, as youre responsible for all activity associated with your account. If you suspect someone else is using your account, notify our Support Team immediately. You must have reached the age of consent for online services in your country to use Knowtical Learning.\nTo participate in most activities on our platform, including purchasing and accessing content or submitting content for publication, you need an account. When creating and maintaining your account, you must provide accurate and complete information, including a valid email address. You are fully responsible for your account and everything that occurs on it, including any harm or damage caused by someone using your account without your permission. This means keeping your password secure. You may not transfer your account to someone else or use someone elses account. If you request access to an account, we will only grant it if you can provide sufficient information to prove you are the owner. In the event of a user\'s death, their account will be closed.\nYou may not share your account login credentials with anyone else. You are responsible for what happens with your account, and Knowtical Learning will not intervene in disputes between students or instructors who have shared account login credentials. Notify us immediately if you learn someone else may be using your account without your permission or if you suspect any other breach of security by contacting our Support Team. We may request information to confirm you are the account owner.\nStudents and instructors must be at least 18 years old to create an account on Knowtical Learning and use our services. If you are younger than 18 but above the age of consent for online services in your country, you may not set up an account but can invite a parent or guardian to open an account to help you access appropriate content. If you are below this age of consent, you may not create a Knowtical Learning account. If we discover you have created an account in violation of these rules, we will terminate it. Under our Instructor Terms, you may be requested to verify your identity before submitting content for publication on Knowtical Learning.\nYou can terminate your account at any time by following the steps outlined in our Privacy Policy to understand what happens when you terminate your account.\n2. Content Enrollment and Lifetime Access\nWhen you enroll in a course or other content, you receive a license from us to view it via the Knowtical Learning platform and services. This license is for personal use only and cannot be transferred or resold in any way. We generally grant you lifetime access, except when content must be disabled due to legal or policy reasons or for enrollments via Subscription Plans.\nUnder our Instructor Terms, when instructors publish content on Knowtical Learning, they grant Knowtical Learning a license to offer that content to students. This means we have the right to sublicense the content to enrolled students. As a student, when you enroll in a course or other content, whether free or paid, you are getting a license from Knowtical Learning to view the content via our platform and services. Content is licensed, not sold, to you. This license does not give you any right to resell the content in any manner, including by sharing account information or illegally downloading and sharing it.\nIn legal terms, Knowtical Learning grants you (as a student) a limited, non-exclusive, non-transferable license to access and view the content for which you have paid all required fees, solely for your personal, non-commercial, educational purposes through our services, in accordance with these Terms and any conditions or restrictions associated with the content. All other uses are expressly prohibited. You may not reproduce, redistribute, transmit, assign, sell, broadcast, rent, share, lend, modify, adapt, edit, create derivative works of, sublicense, or otherwise transfer or use any content unless we give you explicit permission in a written agreement signed by an authorized Knowtical Learning representative. This also applies to content you can access via any of our APIs.\nWe generally provide a lifetime access license to our students when they enroll in a course or other content. However, we reserve the right to revoke any license to access and use content at any time if we decide or are obligated to disable access due to legal or policy reasons, such as if the content is subject to a copyright complaint or violates our Trust & Safety Guidelines. This lifetime access license does not apply to enrollments via Subscription Plans or to add-on features and services associated with the content. For example, instructors may decide at any time to no longer provide teaching assistance or Q&A services related to the content. To be clear, lifetime access is to the course content but not to the instructor.\nInstructors may not grant licenses to their content to students directly, and any such direct license is null and void and a violation of these Terms.\n3. Payments, Credits, and Refunds\nWhen you make a payment, you agree to use a valid payment method. If you arent satisfied with your content, Knowtical Learning offers a 30-day refund or credit for most content purchases.\n3.1 Pricing\nThe prices of content on Knowtical Learning are determined based on the terms of the Instructor Terms and our Promotions Policy. In some instances, the price of content offered on the Knowtical Learning website may differ from the price offered on our mobile or TV applications due to mobile platform providers pricing systems and their policies around implementing sales and promotions.\nWe occasionally run promotions and sales for our content, during which certain content is available at discounted prices for a set period. The price applicable to the content will be the price at the time you complete your purchase (at checkout). Any price offered for particular content may also be different when you are logged into your account compared to when you are not registered or logged in, as some promotions are available only to new users.\nIf you are logged into your account, the listed currency you see is based on your location when you created your account. If you are not logged in, the price currency is based on your current location. We do not enable users to see pricing in other currencies.\nIf you are located in a country where use and sales tax, goods and services tax, or value-added tax is applicable to consumer sales, we are responsible for collecting and remitting that tax to the proper tax authorities. Depending on your location, the price you see may include such taxes, or tax may be added at checkout.\n3.2 Payments\nYou agree to pay the fees for content you purchase and authorize us to charge your debit or credit card or process other payment methods (such as Boleto, SEPA, direct debit, or mobile wallet) for those fees. Knowtical Learning works with payment service providers to offer you the most convenient payment methods in your country and to keep your payment information secure. We may update your payment methods using information provided by our payment service providers. Check our Privacy Policy for more details.\nWhen you make a purchase, you agree not to use an invalid or unauthorized payment method. If your payment method fails and you still get access to the content you enrolled in, you agree to pay the corresponding fees within 30 days of notification from us. We reserve the right to disable access to any content for which we have not received adequate payment.\n3.3 Refunds and Refund Credits\nIf the content you purchased is not what you expected, you can request a refund within 30 days of your purchase. This refund option does not apply to Subscription Plan purchases, which are covered in Section 8.4 (Payments and Billing) below. We reserve the right to apply your refund as a refund credit or a refund to your original payment method, at our discretion, depending on the capabilities of our payment service providers, the platform from which you purchased your content (website, mobile, or TV app), and other factors. No refund is due if you request it after the 30-day guarantee time limit has passed. However, if content you previously purchased is disabled for legal or policy reasons, you are entitled to a refund beyond this 30-day limit. Knowtical Learning also reserves the right to refund students beyond the 30-day limit in cases of suspected or confirmed account fraud.\nTo request a refund, follow the steps outlined in our Support Page. As detailed in the Instructor Terms, instructors agree that students have the right to receive these refunds.\nIf we decide to issue refund credits to your account, they will be automatically applied to your next content purchase on our website but cannot be used for purchases in our mobile or TV applications. Refund credits may expire if not used within the specified period and have no cash value, unless otherwise required by applicable law.\nAt our discretion, if we believe you are abusing our refund policy, such as if youve consumed a significant portion of the content you want to refund or if youve previously refunded the content, we reserve the right to deny your refund, restrict you from future refunds, ban your account, and/or restrict all future use of our services. If we ban your account or disable your access to content due to your violation of these Terms or our Trust & Safety Guidelines, you will not be eligible for a refund. Additional information on our refund policy is available on our Support Page.\n3.4 Gift and Promotional Codes\nKnowtical Learning or our partners may offer gift and promotional codes to students. Certain codes may be redeemed for gift or promotional credits applied to your Knowtical Learning account, which can then be used to purchase eligible content on our platform, subject to the terms included with your codes. Other codes may be directly redeemable for specific content. Gift and promotional credits cannot be used for purchases in our mobile or TV applications.\nThese codes and credits, as well as any promotional value linked to them, may expire if not used within the period specified in your Knowtical Learning account. Gift and promotional codes offered by Knowtical Learning may not be refunded for cash unless otherwise specified in the terms included with your codes or as required by applicable law. Gift and promotional codes offered by a partner are subject to that partners refund policies. If you have multiple saved credit amounts, Knowtical Learning may determine which credits to apply to your purchase. Check out our Support Page and any terms included with your codes for more details.\n4. Content and Behavior Guidelines\nYou may only utilize Knowtical Learning for lawful purposes. You are accountable for all the content you post on our platform. Ensure that the reviews, questions, posts, courses, and other content you upload adhere to our Trust & Safety Guidelines and legal requirements, and respect the intellectual property rights of others. We reserve the right to suspend your account for repeated or significant violations. If you believe someone is infringing your copyright on our platform, please inform us.\nYou may not utilize or establish an account on Knowtical Learning for unlawful purposes. Your utilization of our platform and conduct must comply with applicable local or national laws or regulations in your country. You are solely responsible for understanding and complying with these laws and regulations.\nAs a student, our platform allows you to engage with instructors of courses or other content you are enrolled in by asking questions and posting reviews. For certain content, instructors may invite you to submit content as part of assessments. Do not post or submit any content that is not your own.\nAs an instructor, you can submit content for publication on the platform and communicate with enrolled students. In both cases, you must abide by the law and respect the rights of others: you cannot post any course, question, answer, review, or other content that violates applicable local or national laws or regulations in your country. You are solely responsible for any courses, content, and actions you post or take via the platform and Services and their consequences. Ensure you understand all copyright restrictions outlined in the Instructor Terms before submitting any content for publication on Knowtical Learning.\nIf we are notified that your content violates the law or the rights of others, or if we discover that your content or behavior violates our Trust & Safety Guidelines, or if we believe your content or behavior is unlawful, inappropriate, or objectionable, we may remove your content from our platform. Knowtical Learning complies with copyright laws. Refer to our Intellectual Property Policy for further information.\nKnowtical Learning retains discretion in enforcing these Terms and our Trust & Safety Guidelines. We may restrict or terminate your access to our platform and Services or ban your account at any time, with or without notice, for any reason, including violations of these Terms, failure to pay fees, fraudulent activities, extended inactivity, technical issues, suspected fraudulent or illegal activities, or at our sole discretion. Upon termination, we may delete your account and content and prevent further access to our platforms and services. Your content may still be available on the platforms even if your account is terminated or suspended. You agree that we bear no liability for such actions.\nIf a user has posted content that infringes your copyright or trademark rights, please inform us. Our Instructor Terms require instructors to comply with the law and respect intellectual property rights. For guidance on filing a copyright or trademark infringement claim, refer to our Intellectual Property Policy.\n5. Knowtical Learning\'s Rights to Your Content\nYou retain ownership of the content you post to our platform, including your courses. We may share your content with others via any media, including promotional activities on external websites.\nThe content you post, including courses, remains yours. By posting content, you grant Knowtical Learning the right to reuse and share it, while you retain ownership rights. If you are an instructor, ensure you understand the content licensing terms outlined in the Instructor Terms.\nWhen you post content, comments, questions, reviews, or submit ideas and suggestions for improvements, you authorize Knowtical Learning to use and share this content across platforms and media, with the right to modify or edit it as necessary.\nIn legal terms, by posting content, you grant us a worldwide, non-exclusive, royalty-free license to use, copy, reproduce, adapt, modify, publish, transmit, display, and distribute your content. You also waive any privacy or publicity rights applicable to these uses. You represent and warrant that you have the necessary rights to authorize us to use your content without compensation.\n6. Using Knowtical Learning at Your Own Risk\nAnyone can use Knowtical Learning to create and publish content, facilitating interactions between instructors and students for teaching and learning. Like other platforms, there are risks, and you use Knowtical Learning at your own risk.\nWe do not review or edit content for legal issues and cannot determine its legality. We do not guarantee the reliability, validity, accuracy, or truthfulness of content. By accessing content, you assume any risks associated with it.\nYou may encounter content that you find objectionable while using our Services. Knowtical Learning is not liable for your access to or enrollment in any course or other content. You acknowledge and assume any risks associated with accessing such content.\nExercise caution when sharing personal information during interactions with others on our platform. While we restrict the types of information instructors may request from students, we cannot control how users handle information obtained from others. Do not share personal information for your safety.\nWe do not employ instructors and are not liable for interactions between instructors and students. We are not responsible for disputes, claims, 